      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation performed across three systematically refined meshes (4.2M, 12.1M, 31.6M cells, refinement ratio r=1.44). GCI for normalized index of hemolysis: 1.8% (fine-to-medium), 3.1% (medium-to-coarse). Asymptotic convergence ratio 0.97 confirms mesh independence. Exceeds MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must be documented and traceable; boundary conditions in simulation must match within stated tolerances per ASME V&V 40-2018.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted at FDA CDRH flow loop facility. Inlet flow rates (2–6 L/min) and rotational speeds (2400–3600 RPM) match CFD boundary conditions within ±1.5% and ±10 RPM respectively. Temperature maintained at 37°C ± 0.5°C. All conditions documented in test protocol TP-FDA-CPB-2024."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation metric u_val) must be computed for primary QoI at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) predicted within 12.4% of experimental mean across 5 operating points (mean absolute error 0.0031 g/100L). Pressure head predicted within 4.7% RMS. Validation metric u_val = 0.14 computed per ASME V&V 20-2009 framework. All comparisons within acceptance band."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI used in validation (NIH, RH index) must be directly relevant to the COU decision metric per ASME V&V 40-2018.",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) computed via power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.). RH index derived directly from NIH for predicate comparison. Both QoIs map directly to the COU acceptance criterion (RH < 1). No surrogate or proxy metrics used."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must address the same device class, flow regime, and operating envelope as the COU per ASME V&V 40-2018.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the same geometric family as the CPB device under evaluation. Operating envelope (2–6 L/min, 2400–3600 RPM) encompasses all 5 COU flow-speed combinations. Blood analogue fluid (glycerol-water, viscosity matched to 37°C whole blood) used in experiments."
    },
    {
